    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>WHEN THE BLADE PROKS</font>, By Telmah</b><br><br>I got my blade on 19 and it didn't prok and when I reached 20 it did.  So that's the key level of when the blade proks.  Sorta bad for a bard who is already taking alot of heat from his songs, but for soloing it is great.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>BARD OF WAR, POVAR</font>, By Semerien</b><br><br>As regards to when this blade starts to proc, I got mine at lvl 20 and it was proccing right away.  Not sure what exact lvl it will start procing but at least it's not one of those lvl 45 weapons.  Be warned:  Do not use in dungeons, or if grouped with an enchanter.  The effect is aoe and cancels mez instantly.  Also works as a mean taunt, so be wary.  I just used it to get my piercing up, for it's speed.  Frankly, think this weapon would be a lot better without a proc at all .<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>FINGERS OF FIRE</font>, By Kellina</b><br><br>Yes this spell is an AE spell, it does 28 dam to all the creatures around the caster.  It's a nice weapon but the effect makes it suck, for high lvls where enchanters are needed greatly.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>BARD </font>, By Sharona stalwart</b><br><br>I have this weapon in my arsenal.  While fighting in Mistmoore, our enchanter complained of AE spells cancelling his mez.
Does this blade proc an AE, or was our druid casting a DOT without us realizing ? <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>DROP INFO</font>, By Torch strongwill</b><br><br>This item drops off the Strathbone Runelord in Kaesora.  I believe it is the common.<br><hr size='1'></td>
